b'FACULTY POSITIONS'
b'Postdoctoral Research Associate \xe2\x80\x93 Mechanical Engineering (Job ID #101533)\nDepartment:\xc2\xa0Engineering/Mechanical and Industrial Engineering\nCategory:\xc2\xa0Postdoc Res Assoc\nLocation:\xc2\xa0Chicago\nClose Date:\xc2\xa004/30/2019'
b'Description:\nThe Department of Mechanical and Industrial Engineering (MIE) at University of Illinois at Chicago (UIC) is seeking applications for Postdoctoral Research Associate to conduct research in the area of complex fluid mechanics and fluid dynamics and to assist in developing and testing objectives.'
b'Duties:\nApplicants are expected to have a strong foundation in Fluid mechanics and Fluid dynamics. Candidates with experience on suspension flows and/or flow over porous media are preferred. MATLAB and Machine shop experience are a plus. Excellent communication and written skills are required along with demonstrated success in previous academic research. Additionally, the selected candidate will be expected to oversee students, write reports and publish peer-reviewed journal articles.'
b'The position is available immediately.'
b'Outstanding candidates are invited to submit a letter of application detailing their relevant background, providing the names and e-mail addresses of at least three references, a CV, and copies of relevant reprints and pre-prints.'
b'Send the application (single PDF file) to Dr. Parisa Mirbod (pmirbod@uic.edu). Send email to Dr. Parisa Mirbod for more information about the research program.'
b'pmirbod@uic.edu'
b'Qualifications:\nThe Postdoctoral Research Associate must have a PhD in an engineering discipline, good mechanical design skills, and experience in technologies such as MRI, and/or PIV.'
b'The University of Illinois at Chicago is an Equal Opportunity, Affirmative Action employer. Minorities, women, veterans and individuals with disabilities are encouraged to apply'
b'The University of Illinois conducts background checks on all job candidates upon acceptance of contingent offer of employment. Background checks will be performed in compliance with the Fair Credit Reporting Act.'
b'Apply online at\xc2\xa0https://jobs.uic.edu/job-board/job-details?jobID=101533&job=postdoctoral-research-associate-mechanical-engineering.'
b'https://jobs.uic.edu/job-board/job-details?jobID=101533&job=postdoctoral-research-associate-mechanical-engineering'
b'PhD Research Assistant \xe2\x80\x93 Mechanical Engineering (Job ID #101525)\nDepartment:\xc2\xa0Engineering/Mechanical and Industrial Engineering\nCategory:\xc2\xa0Graduate Assistant\nLocation:\xc2\xa0Chicago\nClose Date:\xc2\xa005/31/2019'
b'Description:\nThe Department of Mechanical and Industrial Engineering (MIE) at the University of Illinois at Chicago (UIC) is seeking\xc2\xa0applications for three highly motivated PhD students to conduct research in the area of complex fluid mechanics and fluid dynamics.'
b'Duties:\nApplicants are expected to have a strong foundation in Fluid mechanics and Fluid dynamics.'
b'Qualifications:\nCandidates with experience on suspension flows and/or flow over porous media are preferred. MATLAB and Machine shop experience are a plus. Excellent communication and written skills are required along with demonstrated success in previous academic research. The candidate will have the opportunity to learn both the theoretical and experimental works related to complex flows over porous media using PIV and MRI.'
b'The appointment includes a stipend and full tuition. Outstanding candidates are invited to submit a letter of application detailing their relevant background, providing the names and e-mail addresses of at least three references, a CV, and copies of relevant reprints and pre-prints.'
b'Send the application (single PDF file) to Dr. Parisa Mirbod (pmirbod@uic.edu). Send email to Dr. Parisa Mirbod for more information about the research program.'
b'pmirbod@uic.edu'
b'The University of Illinois at Chicago is an Equal Opportunity, Affirmative Action employer. Minorities, women, veterans and individuals with disabilities are encouraged to apply'
